        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued November 24 at 4:56PM CST by NWS Houston/Galveston TX</headline>
        <description>At 455 PM CST, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 7
miles west of Crockett, moving northeast at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Crockett, Grapeland, Latexo, Weches, Mound City, and Salmon.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Tornado Watch remains in effect until 700 PM CST for southeastern
Texas.</instruction>
